            en: "<span style=\"font-size: 25px;\"><b>Preface</b></span><br>Praise be to Allah, the only One worthy of worship; I bear witness that He is the sole deity. I testify that Muhammad and Jesus Christ are messengers from Allah, may the prayers and blessings of the Lord be upon them. In this book, it is the sacred texts that speak. With appeal, Muhammad Haydaraâ€™s work stands out for its degree of argumentation and relevance. It is good to invite oneâ€™s neighbor (non-believer) to become Muslim, but it is better that it be certified, assured, and textual.<br><br>Today, Muhammad Haydara gives believers the opportunity to defend their religion, strengthens the faith of many Muslims that Islam is the truth, and invites us to call non-Muslims to explore Islam. Allah says in the Qurâ€™an, Surah An-Nahl, verse 125: â€œInvite to the way of your Lord with wisdom and good instruction, and argue with them in a way that is bestâ€ (Sahih International). Of course, this can be done; one may disagree and have points of divergence, but this does not prevent living in peace, consideration, and social harmony.<br><br>The author does not engage in an attack here, but in a comparative study, a warning. This makes the path of salvation an invitation to its reader to enter the serious realm of faith. This book reveals the True Path that leads to Salvation and is the key to paradise.<br><br>The first part is dedicated to a review of the foundations of Islam and a brief look at Christianity. It then addresses profound questions about human existence, the meaning of our creation, our destiny, majestically illuminating the path to Salvation. After that comes a section of interest to Christians. The second and final part is devoted to the path of salvation, consisting of several chapters that include a call and a reminder. Let us explore the Qurâ€™an and the Bible together!<br><br>Sheikh Abdallah Niass,<br><br>CEO of Al Mouyassar Institute<br>",
