            en: "<b>INCLUSION</b><br>Dear reader, it is therefore clear, as you must have discovered, that there is a difference between what Jesus teaches and what some (Christians) teach about Jesus. If you are now able to believe in One God and that Jesus, the son of Mary, is a Prophet, why not take a further step by admitting that Muhammad (peace be upon him) is the Final Messenger? You will lose nothing; on the contrary, you will gain much more.<br><br>As a Muslim, you are obligated to believe in Moses, Jesus, Muhammad, and all the other prophets. The truth has been revealed to you today, and you are free to revive your reason and accept it. May God deliver us from falsehood.<br><br>(Qurâ€™an 9/31) <b>â€œThey have taken their rabbis and monks, as well as the Messiah, son of Mary, as lords besides God, though they were commanded to worship only One God. There is no deity except Him! Glory be to Him! He is far above what they associate with Him.â€</b><br><br>(Mark 12) <b>â€œ28 One of the teachers of the law, hearing their discussion and seeing that Jesus had answered the Sadducees well, approached and asked him, â€˜Which is the first of all the commandments?â€™ 29 Jesus replied, â€˜The first is this: Hear, O Israel, the Lord our God is one Lord. 30 And you shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, with all your mind, and with all your strength.â€™â€</b><br><br>Just as Moses said in (Deuteronomy 6/4), Jesus Christ repeats it in (Mark 12/29).<br><br>There are also Christians who reject the Trinity, but Jesus is the son of God, they sayâ€”here is the term that troubles them. Let us therefore concern ourselves with these terms:<br>",
