            en: "<b>WHO IS JESUS?</b><br>Before giving our opinions, let us hear from the Scriptures:<br><br>(John 18/20) <b>â€œJesus answered him: I have spoken openly to the world; I have always taught in the synagogue and in the temple, where all the Jews gather, and I have said nothing in secret.â€</b><br><br>Jesus says that he is a prophet, a messenger sent by God.<br><br>(John 17/3) <b>â€œNow this is eternal life: that they know You, the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom You have sent.â€</b><br><br>(John 20/21) <b>â€œJesus said to them again: Peace be with you! As the Father has sent me, I also send you.â€</b><br><br>(Matthew 13/57) <b>â€œBut Jesus said to them: A prophet is not dishonored except in his own country and in his own house.â€</b><br><br>(Matthew 21/10-11) <b>â€œWhen he entered Jerusalem, the whole city was stirred, and people said: Who is this? The crowds answered: This is Jesus, the prophet from Nazareth in Galilee.â€</b><br><br>(Luke 24/19) <b>â€œHe said to them: What? They answered him: What happened concerning Jesus of Nazareth, who was a prophet powerful in deeds and words before God and all the people.â€</b><br><br>(John 5/30) <b>â€œI can do nothing on my own: as I hear, I judge, and my judgment is just, because I seek not my own will but the will of Him who sent me.â€</b><br><br>(John 9/17) <b>â€œAnd there was division among them. They said again to the blind man: What do you say about him, since he opened your eyes? He replied: He is a prophet.â€</b><br><br>(John 8/40) <b>â€œI am a man who has told you the truth, which I heard from God.â€</b><br><br>(John 5/24) <b>â€œTruly, truly, I say to you, whoever hears my word and believes in Him who sent me has eternal life and does not come into judgment but has passed from death to life.â€</b><br><br>(Matthew 15/24) <b>â€œHe answered: I was sent only to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.â€</b><br><br>(John 17/21) <b>â€œThat all may be one, as You, Father, are in me, and I in You, that they also may be one in us, so that the world may believe that You sent me.â€</b><br><br>(John 12/44) <b>â€œJesus cried out: Whoever believes in me believes not in me but in Him who sent me.â€</b><br><br>(John 4/19) <b>â€œThe woman said to him: Lord, I see that you are a prophet.â€</b><br><br>The Qurâ€™an says about Jesus:<br><br>(Qurâ€™an 3/49) <b>â€œAnd he will be a messenger to the Children of Israel.â€</b><br><br>(Qurâ€™an 5/75) <b>â€œThe Messiah, son of Mary, was only a messenger. Messengers came before him. His mother was a truthful woman. Both ate food. See how We make the signs clear to them, yet see how they turn away.â€</b><br><br>(Qurâ€™an 4/171) <b>â€œO People of the Book (Christians), do not exaggerate in your religion, and do not say about God except the truth. The Messiah, Jesus, son of Mary, is only a messenger of God, His word that He sent to Mary, and a spirit from Him. So believe in God and His messengers.â€</b><br><br>(Qurâ€™an 5/72) <b>â€œIndeed, those who say, â€˜God is the Messiah, son of Mary,â€™ have disbelieved. Yet the Messiah said: â€˜O Children of Israel, worship God, my Lord and your Lord.â€™ Whoever associates others with God, God has forbidden him Paradise, and his refuge will be the Fire. For the wrongdoers, there are no helpers.â€</b><br><br>(Qurâ€™an 61/6) <b>â€œAnd when Jesus, son of Mary, said: â€˜O Children of Israel, I am truly a messenger of God sent to youâ€¦â€™â€</b><br><br>(Qurâ€™an 3/64) <b>â€œSay: â€˜O People of the Book, come to a common word between us and you: that we worship none but God, associate nothing with Him, and take not one another as lords besides God.â€™ If they turn away, say: â€˜Bear witness that we are those who submit.â€™â€</b><br><br>Thus, from these clear and evident demonstrations, except to the eyes of one who is blind, prefers misguidance, and cares not for his salvation, we conclude that Jesus is a messenger of God, sent by God, and a servant of God. He is not God, nor one of the three persons of the Trinity, nor a God incarnate. If Jesus were truly God, whom would he have feared to make this declaration: <b>â€œI am God, worship meâ€</b>? Yet God openly declared that He is God in: (Isaiah 46/9) <b>â€œRemember what happened long ago; for I am God, and there is no other; I am God, and there is none like Me.â€</b><br><br>Let us remember that once we err regarding divinity, all our actions will be in vain. So, let us seek the true One, the One who deserves worship, the Supreme Being who created us and merits our supplication by essence and excellence. This leads to a question:<br>",
