            en: "<b>The Quran</b><br>The Quran is the sacred book of Islam, the word of God revealed to the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) without any doubt or dispute. The Quran comprises 114 surahs, consisting of 320,015 letters grouped into 77,439 words, with an estimated total of 6,236 verses.<br><br>(Quran 56) <b>â€˜Indeed, it is a noble Quran, in a Register well-protected; none touch it except the purified, [it is] a revelation from the Lord of the worlds.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 55:2) <b>â€˜He has taught the Quran.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 7:9) <b>â€˜Indeed, this Quran guides to that which is most suitable and gives good tidings to the believers who do righteous deeds that they will have a great reward.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 72:1) <b>â€˜Say, â€œIt has been revealed to me that a group of the jinn listened and said, â€˜Indeed, we have heard an amazing Quran.â€™â€â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 10:37) <b>â€˜And it was not [possible] for this Quran to be produced by other than Allah, but [it is] a confirmation of what was before it and a detailed explanation of the [former] Scripture, about which there is no doubt, from the Lord of the worlds.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 15:9) <b>â€˜Indeed, it is We who sent down the Quran, and indeed, We will be its guardian.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 17:9) <b>â€˜Indeed, this Quran guides to that which is most suitable and gives good tidings to the believers who do righteous deeds that they will have a great reward.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 17:41) <b>â€˜And We have certainly diversified [the contents] in this Quran that they may be reminded, but it does not increase them except in aversion.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 17:88) <b>â€˜Say, â€œIf mankind and the jinn gathered in order to produce the like of this Quran, they could not produce the like of it, even if they were to each other assistants.â€â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 20:2-3) <b>â€˜We have not sent down the Quran to you to cause you distress, but only as a reminder for those who fear [Allah].â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 4:82) <b>â€˜Then do they not reflect upon the Quran? If it had been from [any] other than Allah, they would have found within it much contradiction.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 26:192-195) <b>â€˜And indeed, it is [a revelation] from the Lord of the worlds. The Trustworthy Spirit has brought it down upon your heart, [O Muhammad], that you may be of the warners, in a clear Arabic language.â€™</b><br><br>(Quran 2:23-24) <b>â€˜And if you are in doubt about what We have sent down upon Our Servant, then produce a surah the like thereof and call upon your witnesses other than Allah, if you should be truthful. But if you do notâ€”and you will never be able toâ€”then fear the Fire, whose fuel is men and stones, prepared for the disbelievers.â€™</b><br><br>The Holy Quran is the only book in the world, entirely of divine origin, that has never been altered by humans, events, or time. It is not fitting for a work as sublime and prestigious as this, emanating from Allah, the Creator and Lord of the universe, to suffer any violation. The sacred Book of the Muslims was not authored by the Prophet Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him, as he was illiterate, like many people of his time. Such a masterpiece, in every sense of the word, could not have originated from a human being, for the knowledge it contains transcends human understanding. The Quran is, indeed, a teaching of truth against which all the false certainties of the world falter. The Quran gathers the words of Allah, revelations transmitted by the angel Gabriel to the last Prophet and Messenger of God, Muhammad â€œthe praised,â€ from 610 until his death in 632, intended for all of humanity.<br><br>In the immense primordial silence, before even the breeze touched the skin of the earth, there existed a pure and unalterable truth, a light hidden in the depths of the unseen. At that moment when the universe was but a silent thought in the divine mind, a secret was prepared for humanity. It was not an ordinary word, nor a mere incantation born of human imagination. It was infinite wisdom, a revelation that would emerge from the darkness to illuminate souls and hearts.<br><br>This call to consciousness, this spark of light, came neither from the visible heavens nor from the known lands, but from a higher, transcendent reality, neither of yesterday nor tomorrow, but the eternal presence. When it manifested on this earth, it was not a chance encounter but a meeting prepared in the secrecy of the heavens. This message, so vast that it defies any definition, was woven into human words while preserving its divine and unalterable nature. Thus, it arrived, not as a story, but as a direct dialogue, a living conversation with the Creator, a sacred word whispered into the heart of humanity.<br><br>When these words were spoken, one could not help but feel the divine power manifesting through each syllable. It was not an ordinary book but a word that slipped into the soul, like a ray of light piercing the darkness. With each verse, it was as if God Himself spoke to us, as if every word emanating from it carried divine clarity and infinite wisdom. It was like a call from the heavens descending to earth, a dialogue between the divine and the mortal, a revelation that shakes and transforms those who hear it. The verses were not mere words but waves of eternity that stirred souls, flashes of truth shining deep within consciences.<br><br>Each verse came with infinite richness, like a hidden treasure on every page. It contained stories of ancient peoples, lessons of justice, calls to mercy, and truths about the nature of the soul and the universe. But it was not merely a story of the past; each verse, each word, was a direct response to human questions, a light kindled in the darkness of uncertainties. The unseen became tangible, the mystery unveiled in the clarity of revelation.<br><br>Beyond human comprehension, this message was intended for every sincere heart, every open soul. It was not knowledge reserved for a few but a light accessible to all, a divine word resonating in the hearts of those who embrace it. Through each verse, man meets his Lord, seeing Him not in a place or form but in the depth of words echoing in the soul.<br><br>And so, when reading these verses, it is not merely an intellectual act but an act of communion with the unseen. Each word becomes a meeting, each sentence an exchange, like a secret conversation between humanity and its Creator. A word that is both a breath of light and a depth of wisdom, inviting man to rise, to understand, to draw closer to the One who speaks through it.<br><br>This Book, this unparalleled treasure, is the key to truth, the light in the night of ignorance. It does not merely provide information; it transforms those who approach it with sincerity, inviting them to a spiritual journey beyond the limits of the material world. In this Book, every believer finds their guide, every question its answer, and every soul nourishment from infinite wisdom.<br><br>The name of this Book, which transcends time and history, is the Quran, the divine word, the living Book that remains, eternal and unalterable, through the ages.<br>",
