            en: "<b>Is the Salvation of a Muslim Guaranteed?</b><br>(Quran 43:68-72) <b>'My servants, no fear shall be on you today, nor shall you grieve, those who believed in Our signs and were Muslims. Enter Paradise, you and your spouses, to be honored. There will be circulated among them plates of gold and cups; and therein is whatever the souls desire and what delights the eyes, and you will abide therein eternally. That is the Paradise which you are made to inherit for what you used to do.'</b><br><br>(Quran 46:13-14) <b>'Indeed, those who say, Our Lord is Allah, and then remain steadfastâ€”no fear shall come upon them, nor shall they grieve. Those are the companions of Paradise, abiding eternally therein, as a reward for what they used to do.'</b><br><br>(Matthew 20) <b>'20 Then the mother of Zebedeeâ€™s sons, James and John, came to Jesus with her sons. She knelt before him to ask a favor. 21 What is it you want? he asked. She said, Here are my two sons. Promise that one will sit at your right and the other at your left in your kingdom. 22 Jesus replied, You donâ€™t know what you are asking. Can you drink the cup I am going to drink? Yes, they answered, we can. 23 Jesus said, You will indeed drink from my cup, but to sit at my right or left is not for me to grant. These places belong to those for whom my Father has prepared them.'</b><br><br>Thus, in light of this last verse, Jesus cannot grant paradise to anyone.<br><br>(John 17:3) <b>'Now this is eternal life: that they know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom you have sent.'</b><br><br>Jesus affirms that whoever believes in the one true God and that he (Jesus) is a prophet will have eternal life. In this world, all Muslims believe in the prophethood of Jesus; thus, all Muslims will go to paradise. In other words, the salvation of a Muslim is also guaranteed in the Bible.<br><br>(John 5:24) <b>'Very truly I tell you, whoever hears my word and believes him who sent me has eternal life and will not be judged but has crossed over from death to life.'</b><br><br>(John 7:28) <b>'Then Jesus, still teaching in the temple courts, cried out, You know me, and you know where I am from! I am not here on my own authority, but he who sent me is true. You do not know him.'</b>",
