            en: "<b>Apocalypse</b><br>(2 Peter 3) <b>Â«1 Dear brothers, this is now my second letter to you. In both, I seek to stir up your wholesome thinking by way of reminders, 2 so that you may recall the words spoken beforehand by the holy prophets and the command of our Lord and Savior through your apostles.Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 12:111) <b>Â«Indeed, in their stories, there is instruction for those of understanding. It was not a tale invented, but a confirmation of what was before it and a detailed explanation of all things and guidance and mercy for a people who believe.Â»</b><br>(Quran 17:81) <b>Â«And say, The truth has come, and falsehood has vanished. Indeed, falsehood is ever bound to vanish.Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 74:42-47) <b>Â«What has caused you to enter Hell? They will say, â€œWe were not of those who prayed, nor did we feed the poor. We used to enter into vain discourse with those who spoke nonsense, and we used to deny the Day of Judgment, until there came to us the certainty.â€Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 39:3) <b>Â«Unquestionably, for Allah is the pure religion. And those who take protectors besides Him [say], â€œWe only worship them that they may bring us nearer to Allah.â€ Indeed, Allah will judge between them concerning that over which they differ.Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 2:21) <b>Â«O mankind, worship your Lord, who created you and those before you, that you may become righteous.Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 4:1) <b>Â«O mankind, fear your Lord, who created you from one soul and created from it its mate and dispersed from both of them many men and women. And fear Allah and the wombs [kinship ties]; indeed, Allah is ever, over you, an Observer.Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 20:124-126) <b>Â«And whoever turns away from My remembrance â€“ indeed, he will have a depressed life, and We will gather him on the Day of Resurrection blind. He will say, â€œMy Lord, why have You raised me blind while I was [once] seeing?â€ [Allah] will say, â€œThus did Our signs come to you, and you forgot them; and thus will you this Day be forgotten.â€Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 59:18) <b>Â«O you who have believed, fear Allah. And let every soul look to what it has put forth for tomorrow â€“ and fear Allah. Indeed, Allah is Acquainted with what you do.Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 10:108) <b>Â«Say, â€œO mankind, the truth has come to you from your Lord, so whoever is guided is guided for himself, and whoever goes astray does so to his own detriment. And I am not over you a manager.â€Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 4:170) <b>Â«O mankind, the Messenger has come to you with the truth from your Lord, so believe; it is better for you. But if you disbelieve â€“ then indeed, to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and earth. And ever is Allah Knowing and Wise.Â»</b><br><br>(Quran 4:174) <b>Â«O mankind, there has come to you a conclusive proof from your Lord, and We have sent down to you a clear light.Â»</b><br>Let this little book be among those radiant lights.<br><br>(Quran 35:28) <b>Â«And among people and moving creatures and grazing livestock are various colors similarly. Only those fear Allah, from among His servants, who have knowledge. Indeed, Allah is Exalted in Might and Forgiving.Â»</b><br>May Allah rank us among this category of the wise.<br><br>In short, dear brother, man of God, I invite you to reflect deeply on these essential truths. Free yourself from the false beliefs instilled in you since childhood, and open your eyes, for your salvation depends on your personal choices. There is no verse in the Bible stating, Â«The Christian enters paradise,Â» while the Quran guarantees the promise of paradise for those who follow the straight path.<br><br>Jesus himself said: Â«The one who loves me is the one who keeps my words,Â» and he specified that his mission was only for the children of Israel. So, ask yourself this important question: who came for us, Africans, and for all humanity? The answer lies in the mission of our Prophet Muhammad, peace be upon him, who was sent for everyone without exception, including the unseen world (Quran 72). This is an invitation to reflect on the true path to salvation.<br><br>At the dawn of this conclusion, after exploring these pages steeped in truth, it is now time to pause, reflect on the depth of the shared teachings, and examine your soul. The sacred choice is yours alone: to take a decisive step toward the truth or to let yourself be swayed by the winds of ignorance. The Way of Salvation lies open before you, in your hands, awaiting your decision before death visits us.<br><br>With great joy, we have presented The Way of Salvation, our first book. We are deeply honored to have shared with you this work, which represents the result of years of study and the fruit of days of reflection, discoveries, experiences, and research. This book stands firm as an argument to defend, uphold, and validate Islam, the absolute truth. Through these pages, we have invited you to explore with us the true path that leads to salvation, inner peace, ultimate faith, and spiritual fulfillment.<br><br>This journey, through profound, sensitive, and essential teachings, has been an invitation to deep reflection on topics such as the Prophet Jesus Christ, Islam, compassion, and connection with the divine, among others. We have been deeply moved by the religious encounters and invaluable lessons we have received along our path. Therefore, we express our gratitude to all those who have crossed our way. Thank you, dear teachers, mentors, scholars, and sources of wisdom and inspiration.<br><br>Though young, we hope this book is not seen as the work of mere ignorant youths, for even a mosquito can make a lionâ€™s eye bleed. Thinking about God is a serious and fundamental matter. To ensure our efforts are not in vain, seeking the true God, worthy of worship, must be the goal of every human who believes in life after death. We hope this work has been beneficial to you. All truth comes from God, and any error is from myself. May The Way of Salvation be a source of inspiration, peace, awakening, and transformation for you.<br><br>Amidst abundant deception, the authorâ€™s pen seeks to take its leave. Thus, we reach the culmination of an enriching journey through these teachings, meditations, and studies. If this modest work, The Way of Salvation, finds refuge in the hearts of believers and settles as a gentle light in Muslim homes, then my efforts will not have been in vain. The true reward I seek is not earthly glory but the salvation of the soul. If my words, carried by unwavering sincerity and accompanied by deep reflection, manage to awaken a dormant conscience or illuminate a clouded thought, then my humble mission will be fulfilled. True triumph lies not in human recognition but in fidelity to divine truth, the only force capable of liberating and guiding toward the salvation of soul and body.<br><br>May this humble pen, dipped in the ink of faith, become a torch for those seeking truth. May the sleepless nights spent guarding the truth turn into battles to extinguish the flag of ignorance. If this book, like a lighthouse in the darkness, manages to guide even one soul back to the straight path, then my efforts will be rewarded by Allahâ€™s mercy. Truly, there is no greater success than seeing a heart turn to the Lord, a soul purify itself, and rise toward eternal good.<br><br>I thus place this humble work at the feet of the Almighty, imploring His blessing and infinite mercy. May this modest book, like a drop of water nourishing a barren desert, find its place in the hearts of truth-seekers. May it be for you, dear readers, an oasis of serenity in this troubled world, guiding you to eternal peace, the true peace found only in embracing Islam, the way of salvation. May Godâ€™s light guide your steps, His peace accompany you at every moment, and by His grace, may this work be a springboard to eternal knowledge. I beseech Allah to accept this work, and I pray for righteousness and eternal salvation. (Aameen)",
